    <div class="body">
        <p>Hi everyone.
I've just found a bug in the ZendX_JQuery_View_Helper_DatePicker class in _resolveLocaleToDatePickerFormat() function. I set up zend_locale to en, so first part the result of Zend_Locale_Format::getDateFormat() method is MMM, which is equivalent to M in date() function. The _resolveLocaleToDatePickerFormat() function makes it as 'mmm' not 'M'. The problem is in str_replace() function, because shorter strings are at the beginning of array map, so str_replace() repleaced 3 times 'M' by 'm'.</p>

<p>Hope you know what I mean.</p>

